.TH "LIGHTNING-PEER-INFO" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-peer-info \- show detailed information for a single peer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning peer-info
.I peer_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns connectivity and channel summary for a specific peer.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"peer_id":"...","alias":"...","connected":bool,
 "num_channels":N,"local_sat":N,"remote_sat":N,"features":"..."}
.fi
Returns
.nf
{"error":"not_found"}
.fi
when the peer is unknown.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer-list (1),
.BR lightning-peer-connect (1)
